MBOMBELA – Janet is a grade R teacher and headmistress at Fairyland Nursery School where she has helped build the school for the past 22 years. It has 126 learners ranging from three to six years old, with five teachers to look after them. It started 29 years ago where the old Nelsville clinic used to be. Even though it was still under the administration of Child Welfare then, Fairyland is now an independent non-profit organisation. Also read: What to do when your property gets land-grabbed 